            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Sorry if I was not clear, the screenshot is from the neovim-snap repo not this repo. The automatic flow for neovim releases of snaps should be as follows:\r\n\r\n1. release of neovim occurs\r\n2. trigger the update readme workflow in neovim-snap\r\n3. workflow triggers builds and release\r\n\r\nFor this to occur, an action will need to be added, and two in the neovim-snap repo, workflows need write permissions.\r\n\r\n\r\n________________________________\r\nFrom: bfredl ***@***.***>\r\nSent: Friday, May 5, 2023 5:22:37 PM\r\nTo: neovim/neovim ***@***.***>\r\nCc: Carlos Hernandez ***@***.***>; Mention ***@***.***>\r\nSubject: Re: [neovim/neovim] Automate release of snap (Issue #23496)\r\n\r\n\r\n@hurricanehrndz<https://github.com/hurricanehrndz> Not sure why we need to set permissions for anything on neovim/neovim. anyone can just watch events occurring on this repo externally.\r\n\r\n—\r\nReply to this email directly, view it on GitHub<https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23496#issuecomment-1536897142>, or unsubscribe<https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/ABMJBTOWTLKMG6WR34CCGZTXEWDT3ANCNFSM6AAAAAAXXVDCNM>.\r\nYou are receiving this because you were mentioned.Message ID: ***@***.***>\r\n",
