            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, the \"read and write\" in the screenshot refers to the general permissions of GITHUB_TOKEN on workflows, not the \"workflow\" permission specifically which can only be accessed with a Personal Access Token. You can create a token yourself and request it to be included in the neovim-snap repo.\n\nThat being said, the workflow permission is beyond cursed and I can't get it to work. My advice is to call an external shell script from your workflow and then modify that instead. Would this approach work?",
